deck: Former Vice President of Republic Oil & Natural Gas.
description:
Iron Man: The Iron Age

Simon Krieger was the Vice President of Republic Oil & Natural Gas the company that would become the Roxxon Energy Corporation. Simon along with the rest of Republic Oil & Natural Gas wanted to buy Stark Industries and went to great lengths to try and sabotage the plant to get Tony Stark to sell it. They were even responsible for the deaths of Howard Stark and Maria Stark in hopes that Tony would be to poorly equipped and not up to task for running a company.

Simon's final plan that eventually resulted in his death was to disguise himself as Tony Stark and ransom some of the worlds leader's with the aid of a mercenary group known as the Dogs of War at a secret meeting discussing S.H.I.E.L.D. on board a Helicarrier still being developed. The ultimate goal was to simply ruin Tony Stark's reputation. Simon's plan failed however when his true identity was discovered thanks to Happy Hogan who unmasked Simon on a live video feed and Iron Man who defeated the Dogs of War.

Simon was then brought to jail where he was assassinated in his cell by someone hired by the heads of Republic Oil & Natural Gas.
name: Simon Krieger

deck: An actor who portrayed "Lobster Johnson" in a series of low budget Mexican movies.
description:
Adolfo starred in several low budget Mexican movies as "Lobster Johnson", very loosely based on the exploits of the actual Lobster. In these movies, Lobster Johnson was a corpse that would turn into a Mexican masked wrestler at night.

In 1956, Adolfo encountered a very drunk Hellboy who informed him that Lobster was actually a real person though he was reluctant to believe it.

deck: A supernatural being who married Hellboy during a drunken escapade in Mexico. Her actual name has not been revealed.
description:
Most information about Hellboy's wife, including her name, has not been revealed to the reader. All that is known is that she was "born in Spain, but served in Hell" and that she knew she would be "bound for the burning sea", possibly implying that she was a human who engaged in dark arts that damned her soul. Upon meeting Hellboy, she makes several mentions of him being a king, maybe indicating she knew of his prophesied destiny as the ruler of Pandemonium.

She encountered Hellboy during his drunken trip in Mexico and married him after a night of partying. In the morning, a sober Hellboy noticed her demonic appearance for the first time and the two had an altercation which resulted in her death. (Dark Horse Presents #31 and #32)

She wound up in Hell where she took the form of a snake and waited around the halls of Pandemonium for her husband to join her there, where she hoped to help him fulfill what she believed to be his destiny. When he arrived, she subtly influenced him to murder Satan, though he did not realize she was there (Hellboy in Hell #2). Later she confronted him directly, and pushed him to accept his destiny but to do so on his own terms. She said that he could not start a new life before finishing his old one. This lead to Hellboy bringing the apocalypse to Hell and completely overturning the order of the land. She has since gone into hiding. (Hellboy in Hell #9)
